  "texts": [
    "These tools define domain-specific languages for this purpose, such as the XML-based RAIL (Reliable AI Markup Language) [58].",
    "In contrast, Impromptu offers a much simpler mechanism to validate responses based on the traits of the prompt.",
    "This provides an end-to-end traceability between the prompt and its own evaluation.",
    "Additionally, Impromptu facilitates the creation of other validation formulae through prompts built with the DSL itself.",
    "This means only one language is sufficient to create prompts and specify how they should be validated."
  ],
